HEADWORD: Hooked
<hw>Hooked</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the
form of a hook; curvated; <as>as, the <ex>hooked</ex> bill of a
bird</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Provided with a hook or hooks.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>hooked</xex> chariot.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hookedness</ent>⟦br⟧
